---
id: org.dxos.plugin.comments
name: CommentsPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

CommentsPlugin is the **review layer** over ECHO objects (primarily Markdown documents). It renders
two kinds of anchored, attributed annotations and the surfaces that review them:

- **Comment threads** — anchored discussions, with an optional per-thread AI agent that answers and
  may propose document edits.
- **Suggestions** — Google-Docs-style proposed changes authored on per-user branches, surfaced as
  reviewable change-block cards (accept/reject) alongside the comment threads.

It contributes the in-editor comment extension and the suggestion-sources bridge (both
`MarkdownCapabilities.*`), a companion surface listing a subject's threads and suggestions, and the
per-thread agent. It depends on no other plugin: message/thread UI comes from `@dxos/react-ui-thread`,
review/diff primitives from `@dxos/ui-editor`, branch machinery from `@dxos/versioning`, and the
`Thread`/`Message`/`AnchoredTo` schema from `@dxos/types`.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`     |

## External types & capabilities

The suggestion layer composes primitives owned elsewhere; the plugin binds to them rather than
redefining them:

- `Thread`, `Message`, `AnchoredTo` (`@dxos/types`) — the anchored-annotation schema. `AnchoredTo`
  carries an optional `branch` tag scoping an annotation to a review branch (undefined = main).
- `Branch` (`@dxos/versioning`) — a per-user suggestion branch is a `Branch` with `kind: 'suggestion'`
  keyed by author `creator` (DID); `Branch.suggestion`/`Branch.bind` find-or-create and bind it.
- `SuggestionSource`, `trackChanges`, `suggestions({ base })`, `rebaseHunks`, `DiffHunk`, `GroupPolicy`
  (`@dxos/ui-editor`) — the inline diff/overlay primitives. The multi-author overlay and the
  branch-vs-main tracked-change rendering live in the editor; this plugin feeds and reviews them.
- `MarkdownCapabilities.ExtensionProvider` / `MarkdownCapabilities.SuggestionSourcesProvider`
  (`@dxos/plugin-markdown`) — the slots this plugin contributes to.
- `ReviewRenderPolicy` / `ReviewMode` (`@dxos/plugin-versioning`) — the per-user Editing/Suggesting/Viewing
  policy that drives comment/suggestion visibility (`showComments`, `showSuggestions`) in the editor.
- `CollaborationOperation.AcceptChange` / `RejectChange` / `AcceptProposal` (`@dxos/app-toolkit`) —
  the durable cherry-pick/revert ops the review surfaces route accept/reject through.

## Types

```mdl
type AgentMode
  literals: auto | mention
  desc: Per-thread agent firing policy.
```

```mdl
type AgentConfig
  desc: |
    Per-thread agent configuration. Defined in @dxos/types and stored as an optional
    field on Thread.Thread (`agent?`). Absent or disabled means no AI involvement.
  fields:
    enabled: Boolean
    mode: AgentMode
```

```mdl
type AgentIdentity
  desc: |
    Effect/Capability identity of the comment-thread agent, resolved at runtime (not stored on
    threads). The default reads from plugin Settings; tests/stories provide static values. Sole
    source of the agent's display name and @mention token. NOTE: distinct from @dxos/compute's
    `AgentIdentity` service (the suggestion-author DID) — see the naming-collision follow-up.
  fields:
    name: String
    identityDid?: String
    avatar?: String
```

```mdl
type ViewState
  desc: Per-subject view state for the comments companion.
  fields:
    showResolvedThreads: Boolean
```

```mdl
type CommentsState
  desc: |
    In-memory comment UI state (atom). Keyed by subject/object URI.
  fields:
    toolbar: Map<String, Boolean>     # per-object: does the selection overlap a comment?
    drafts: Map<String, AnchoredTo[]> # staged (unsent) threads per subject
    current?: String                  # currently-selected thread URI
```

```mdl
type ResolvedSuggestionBranch
  desc: |
    A resolved `kind:'suggestion'` branch: its author (identity DID) and current content, read live
    from the bound branch doc. The unit the review layer diffs against main.
  fields:
    author: String        # identity DID (Branch.creator)
    content: String       # live branch content
    hue?: String          # the author's palette hue, when known
```

```mdl
type SuggestionGroup
  desc: |
    One reviewable suggestion card: a grouped DiffHunk (via ui-editor `groupHunks`) from a single
    author, anchored in the base (main) text and tinted with the author's colour.
  extends: DiffHunk
  fields:
    author: String
    colour: String
```

## Services

```mdl
service AgentRunner
  desc: |
    Capability that executes one agent turn for a thread + subject. Default implementation
    performs one LanguageModel.generateText call with edit tools registered per turn
    (editAnchoredRange, updateDocument). Stub implementations are used in storybook + tests.
  methods:
    run(input: { thread: Thread, subject: Obj.Any }) -> Effect<void>
```

```mdl
service ExtensionProvider
  desc: |
    Implements MarkdownCapabilities.ExtensionProvider (defined by @dxos/plugin-markdown).
    Returns CodeMirror extensions that: sync anchored comment threads with editor ranges,
    scope visible comments to the active review branch (AnchoredTo.branch), track
    selection/comment overlap into CommentsState.toolbar, open the comments companion on
    marker click, honour the review policy (`showComments` hides them; a `suggestionBranch`
    prohibits inline comment creation), and resolve anchors against the editor-bound Text
    (main or the branch doc in Branch view).
```

```mdl
service SuggestionSourcesProvider
  desc: |
    Implements MarkdownCapabilities.SuggestionSourcesProvider. A headless React component that
    enumerates a document's active `kind:'suggestion'` branches, binds each to read its live
    content, and reports the resolved `SuggestionSource[]` up to the markdown editor's ambient
    overlay — so the editor renders every author's suggestions without importing plugin-comments
    (the dependency runs the other way). Backs both the editor overlay and the review companion.
```

## Operations

```mdl
op Create
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.create
  desc: Create a (staged) comment thread anchored to a subject; seeds CommentsState.drafts.
  input: { subject: Obj.Any, anchor?: String, name?: String, branch?: String }

op AddMessage
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.add-message
  desc: |
    Append a user message to a thread (promoting a staged draft to active). Evaluates the
    agent trigger gate and schedules RespondToThread when it passes.
  input: { subject: Obj.Any, anchor: AnchoredTo, sender: Actor, text: String }

op Delete
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.delete
  desc: Delete a thread + its anchor. Undoable via Restore.
  input: { anchor: AnchoredTo, subject: Obj.Any, thread?: Thread }
  output: { thread?: Thread, anchor?: AnchoredTo }

op Restore
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.restore
  desc: Inverse of Delete.
  input: { thread: Thread, anchor: AnchoredTo }

op DeleteMessage
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.delete-message
  desc: Delete a single message from a thread. Undoable via RestoreMessage.
  input: { anchor: AnchoredTo, subject: Obj.Any, messageId: String }
  output: { message?: Message, messageIndex?: Number }

op RestoreMessage
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.restore-message
  desc: Inverse of DeleteMessage.
  input: { anchor: AnchoredTo, message: Message, messageIndex: Number }

op ToggleResolved
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.toggle-resolved
  desc: Toggle thread.status between active and resolved.
  input: { thread: Thread }

op Select
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.select
  desc: Set the currently-selected thread (CommentsState.current); omit `current` to clear it.
  input: { current?: String }

op RespondToThread
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.respond-to-thread
  desc: Run one agent turn against a thread. Scheduled by AddMessage when the gate passes.
  input: { thread: Ref<Thread>, subject: Ref<Obj.Any> }

op SetAgentConfig
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.set-agent-config
  desc: Mutate thread.agent. Undefined config means off.
  input: { thread: Ref<Thread>, config?: AgentConfig }

op CreateProposals
  key: org.dxos.plugin.comments.operation.create-proposals
  desc: |
    Materialise assistant-proposed document edits as NEW proposal-block comment
    threads, one per diff, each anchored to the document at the diff's cursor range.
  input: { doc: Ref<Markdown.Document>, diffs: String[] }
```

> Accept/reject of suggestions and proposals is NOT a plugin-comments operation: the review surfaces
> route them through the durable `CollaborationOperation.AcceptChange` / `RejectChange` /
> `AcceptProposal` ops (`@dxos/app-toolkit`), which cherry-pick/revert the hunk against the author's
> branch and main. A comment left on the base while reviewing resolves its target branch from
> `AnchoredTo.branch ?? reviewBranch`.

## Components

```mdl
component CommentsArticle
  desc: |
    Companion surface (role 'article', linkedSegment 'comments') for a host object. Lists comment
    threads (via an AnchoredTo query + in-memory drafts) AND the suggestion review cards
    (via Suggestions). Tabs switch unresolved / all. Comment threads render via @dxos/react-ui-thread
    Thread.* with an injected Object tile; a comment's Accept-change routes through the durable
    CollaborationOperation.AcceptChange.
  props:
    attendableId?: String
    subject: Obj.Any

component Suggestions
  desc: |
    Review companion for a document's `kind:'suggestion'` branches. Renders SuggestionSources
    (headless, one bound probe per active suggestion branch) to resolve live content, builds
    per-author SuggestionSource[] (buildSuggestionSources), and renders SuggestionThread cards.
    Reactive: a card appears/updates as its author edits and disappears when accepted/rejected
    empties the branch. Routes accept/reject to the durable ops (services: []).
  props:
    document?: VersionedObject
    base: String                      # main content each suggestion is diffed against
    group?: GroupPolicy
    authorLabels?: Map<String, String>
    authorHues?: Map<String, String>
  emits:
    accept: { group: SuggestionGroup }
    reject: { group: SuggestionGroup }

component SuggestionThread
  desc: |
    Renders one author's grouped changes as change-block tiles (before/after) with hover
    Accept/Reject, tinted with the author's hue. Built on @dxos/react-ui-thread Message.* with a
    ContentBlock.Change tile; renders nothing when empty.
  props:
    base: String
    sources: SuggestionSource[]
    group?: GroupPolicy
    authorLabels?: Map<String, String>
    authorHues?: Map<String, String>

component SuggestionSources
  desc: |
    Headless enumerator (render-prop + onResolved callback). Renders one invisible probe per active
    `kind:'suggestion'` branch, binds it, and reports the resolved ResolvedSuggestionBranch[] both
    synchronously (children render-prop, correct on document swap) and post-commit (onResolved, for
    the editor overlay bridge). Contributed to markdown as SuggestionSourcesProvider.
  props:
    document: VersionedObject
    authorHues?: Map<String, String>
    onResolved?: (resolved: ResolvedSuggestionBranch[]) -> void

component AgentToggle
  desc: |
    Per-thread radio popover hung off the thread header. Three states off / mention / auto;
    shows the resolved AgentIdentity.name as a read-only label. Routes through SetAgentConfig.
  props:
    value?: AgentConfig
    agentName: String
  emits:
    change: { config?: AgentConfig }
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Comment threads on objects

  req F-1.1: The plugin MUST contribute a CodeMirror extension via
    MarkdownCapabilities.ExtensionProvider that creates anchored comment threads from
    editor selections and keeps AnchoredTo cursors in sync with edits.

  req F-1.2: The plugin MUST contribute a companion app-graph node (linkedSegment
    'comments', icon 'ph--chat-text--regular') for any commentable object (an ECHO
    object that is NOT a Channel and for which a CommentConfig is registered).

  req F-1.3: The plugin MUST contribute a 'comment' toolbar action for commentable objects,
    disabled when the selection is invalid or already overlaps an existing comment.

  req F-1.4: CommentsArticle MUST list threads anchored to the subject, sorted by the
    registered AnchorSort for the subject typename, with staged drafts appended.

  req F-1.5: Resolving, deleting, and message-deleting MUST route through operations
    (ToggleResolved / Delete / DeleteMessage), never direct schema writes from the view.
    Delete and DeleteMessage MUST be undoable (Restore / RestoreMessage undo mappings).

feat F-2: Per-thread agent configuration

  req F-2.1: Thread schema's optional `agent: AgentConfig` field MUST gate AI involvement;
    absent/disabled means none. No migration required for existing threads.

  req F-2.2: The AgentIdentity service MUST be the sole source of the agent's display name.
    The plugin MUST contribute a default AgentIdentity at activation; hosts override by
    contributing their own earlier in plugin order.

feat F-3: Trigger gate

  req F-3.1: AddMessage MUST evaluate the gate after appending the message and MUST schedule
    (not invoke) RespondToThread when it passes.

  req F-3.2: The gate MUST return true iff ALL hold:
    - thread.agent?.enabled === true
    - message.sender.role !== 'assistant'
    - thread.status !== 'resolved'
    - mode === 'auto' OR text contains '@' + agentName (case-insensitive)

  req F-3.3: The gate MUST NOT fire on assistant messages (self-loop guard) and MUST NOT
    retroactively respond to prior messages when enabled mid-conversation.

feat F-4: Agent runner

  req F-4.1: The runner MUST be a Capability so storybook/tests can swap a stub without
    changing call sites.

  req F-4.2: The default runner MUST execute one LLM turn, appending the response (or a
    synthesized post-tool acknowledgement) as an assistant message on the same thread.

  req F-4.3: When the subject is a Markdown.Document the runner MUST be given edit tools
    (editAnchoredRange, updateDocument); otherwise it MUST only post a chat reply.

  req F-4.4: Assistant messages MUST carry sender = { role: 'assistant', name, identityDid }
    from the resolved AgentIdentity.

  req F-4.5: Runner errors MUST be caught at the operation-handler boundary, logged, and emit
    a `comments.agent.failed` observability event; the user's message MUST remain in the thread.

feat F-5: Presentation via react-ui-thread

  req F-5.1: Comment threads and suggestion cards MUST render with @dxos/react-ui-thread
    Thread.* / Message.*; the plugin MUST NOT re-implement message tiles or the composer.

  req F-5.2: Object/reference and change (before/after) message blocks MUST be rendered by tiles
    injected into Thread.Root (Surface, type AppSurface.CardContent). react-ui-thread MUST stay
    free of @dxos/app-framework.

feat F-6: Independence

  req F-6.1: plugin-comments MUST NOT import @dxos/plugin-thread or @dxos/plugin-markdown source
    (no plugin → plugin deps); cross-plugin wiring is via capabilities only.

  req F-6.2: Storybook sample data MUST use the real @dxos/types Message schema generated via
    @dxos/schema/testing, not bespoke message-entity types.

feat F-7: Suggestion review companion

  req F-7.1: The plugin MUST contribute SuggestionSourcesProvider to
    MarkdownCapabilities.SuggestionSourcesProvider, enumerating a document's active
    `kind:'suggestion'` branches and reporting each branch's live content as a SuggestionSource.

  req F-7.2: Suggestions MUST render one reviewable card per grouped change per author
    (suggestionGroups), reactively appearing/updating as authors edit and disappearing when a
    branch's diff vs main becomes empty.

  req F-7.3: Accept/reject on a card MUST route through the durable
    CollaborationOperation.AcceptChange / RejectChange (services: []) — Accept cherry-picks the
    hunk from the author's branch into main; Reject reverts it on the author's branch. The card
    MUST NOT splice the document directly.

  req F-7.4: Each author's suggestions MUST be tinted with a stable per-author colour
    (suggestionColour): the author's identity hue when known, else a hash of the author DID —
    the same colour used for the author's avatar/tag and the inline editor markers.

feat F-8: Comment / suggestion coexistence

  req F-8.1: Comments MUST be scoped to the active review branch via AnchoredTo.branch: a comment
    tagged with a branch is visible only while that branch is under review (undefined = main).

  req F-8.2: Inline comment creation MUST be prohibited while the editor is bound to a per-user
    suggestion branch (comments live on main / draft branches, not on suggestion drafts).

  req F-8.3: Comment marks/creation MUST honour the review policy's `showComments`: when false the
    comment extension renders nothing and creates nothing.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Auto mode responds to every user message
  given: A thread with agent = { enabled: true, mode: 'auto' }
  when: A user appends a text message via AddMessage
  then:
    - RespondToThread is scheduled exactly once
    - The runner's run is invoked with the thread and subject

test T-2: Mention mode gates on @name
  given: A thread with agent = { enabled: true, mode: 'mention' }, identity.name = 'kai'
  when: A user posts "hello world" then "hey @Kai check this"
  then:
    - The first message does not schedule RespondToThread
    - The second message schedules RespondToThread

test T-3: Self-loop guard
  given: A thread with agent = { enabled: true, mode: 'auto' }
  when: A message with sender.role = 'assistant' is appended
  then: RespondToThread is NOT scheduled

test T-4: Resolved threads do not trigger
  given: A thread with agent.enabled = true and status = 'resolved'
  when: A user appends a message
  then: RespondToThread is NOT scheduled

test T-5: Disabled mid-conversation preserves history
  given: A thread with prior assistant messages
  when: SetAgentConfig is invoked with config = undefined
  then:
    - thread.agent becomes undefined
    - thread.messages is unchanged

test T-6: Delete/restore round-trips
  given: A comment thread with one message
  when: Delete is invoked, then its Restore undo mapping is applied
  then: The thread and its anchor are restored unchanged

test T-7: CommentsArticle lists anchored threads
  given: A subject with two anchored threads (one resolved) and one staged draft
  when: CommentsArticle renders in 'unresolved' mode
  then: The resolved thread is hidden; the active thread and the draft are shown

test T-8: Runner errors do not lose the user message
  given: A thread with agent enabled and a runner stubbed to fail
  when: A user appends a message
  then:
    - The user message persists in the thread
    - A `comments.agent.failed` observability event is emitted
    - No assistant message is appended

test T-9: Multi-author suggestion cards
  given: A document with two active suggestion branches (authors A and B)
  when: Suggestions renders
  then:
    - One card per grouped change per author is shown
    - Each card is tinted with its author's colour
    - A branch whose diff vs main is empty shows no card

test T-10: Accept routes through the durable op
  given: A suggestion card for author A's change
  when: The card's Accept is clicked
  then:
    - CollaborationOperation.AcceptChange is invoked with A's branch
    - The card is dismissed and the document is not spliced directly

test T-11: SuggestionSources resolves reactively without a stale frame
  given: SuggestionSources mounted on document D1 with two suggestion branches
  when: The document prop swaps to D2
  then: onResolved / the render-prop never reports D1's sources for D2 (no stale frame)

test T-12: Comment scoping + prohibition
  given: A document under review of a `kind:'suggestion'` branch
  when: The comment extension renders
  then:
    - Only comments tagged with that branch (or main) are shown
    - Inline comment creation is prohibited on the suggestion branch
    - With policy.showComments = false, no comment marks render
```
